  "text": "The first question that arises is what constitutes a welldesigned performance measure or a BSC [CITATION_1] . Several surveys have discussed some of the same or related questions, for example, the inadequacies in traditional accounting measures and their lack of predictive ability, that is, their missing information on root causes and their inability to capture key business changes, their problems of not reflecting crossfunctional processes, or their inability to influence the financial consequences of different actions [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] .",
